01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:18.000
And still not be above the poverty line

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:26.000
So I just want to point out again that animals and trees and plants don't have moral choices

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:28.000
We have moral choices

01:10:28.000 --> 01:10:34.000
So now we need to talk about how did morality emerge in human evolution

01:10:34.000 --> 01:10:40.000
And again, we have hunter-gatherer brains, we're all tribal creatures

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:44.000
We harmlessly divert that into sports or other things

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:50.000
We less so harmlessly divert that into ideologies and nationalism

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:53.000
And ethnic chauvinism and so on and so forth

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:57.000
And so there's two ways to approach our moral

01:10:57.000 --> 01:11:01.000
One is what's functional, what's best for the individual for the group

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:03.000
And the other is principled

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:07.000
And so you're taking a principled position

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:09.000
